    "800eebd7-962e-4fa6-bc5d-8b818a1ba455": {
      "type": "content-list",
      "blocks": {
        "template--16177341137065__800eebd7-962e-4fa6-bc5d-8b818a1ba455-image-1": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "apply_overlay": false,
            "devices": "mobile_desktop",
            "content_position": "underLeft",
            "subheading": "",
            "title": "",
            "description": "<p><strong>What is something that has surprised you about marriage – perhaps a misconception proven wrong, or an assumption proven right?</strong></p><p>I always had an understanding that marriage and relationships would be hard. That every day would be a battle and that you had to fight for your love but in this relationship it has never been so easy, so calm and so fun. We will be married for coming up to 3 years in August and it has been a delight. Sure, there are difficult times, when dealing with grief and loss for one, but that brought us closer together. Life can be hard, but not our marriage. Marriage is what gets us through it, together.</p><p></p><p><strong>What is one of your favourite moments from your special day?</strong></p><p>Our wedding day was incredible! The happiest moment in our lives! It was filled with so much love, joy and laughter. We got married at St Marys Cathedral in Sydney and I remember standing at the start of the very long aisle while ‘May it be’ by Enya played on the church organs. I remember feeling so happy and excited to meet him at the end of the aisle. A real moment in time.</p>",
            "description_mobile": "<p><strong>What is something that has surprised you about marriage – perhaps a misconception proven wrong, or an assumption proven right?</strong></p><p>I always had an understanding that marriage and relationships would be hard. That every day would be a battle and that you had to fight for your love but in this relationship it has never been so easy, so calm and so fun. We will be married for coming up to 3 years in August and it has been a delight. Sure, there are difficult times, when dealing with grief and loss for one, but that brought us closer together. Life can be hard, but not our marriage. Marriage is what gets us through it, together.</p><p></p><p><strong>What is one of your favourite moments from your special day?</strong></p><p>Our wedding day was incredible! The happiest moment in our lives! It was filled with so much love, joy and laughter. We got married at St Marys Cathedral in Sydney and I remember standing at the start of the very long aisle while ‘May it be’ by Enya played on the church organs. I remember feeling so happy and excited to meet him at the end of the aisle. A real moment in time.</p>",
            "colour_style": "dark",
